content.text: "Ownership code 66" likely refers to `SOC = '66'` (School Ownership Code), which is "High Schools (Public)". Let me now query for the top 5 K-12 campuses by FRPM Count with SOC 66.

input.command:
sqlite3 -header -column "/Users/david/workspace/claimdb/test_dbs/california_schools.sqlite" "
SELECT 
    f.\`School Name\`,
    f.\`FRPM Count (K-12)\`,
    f.\`Enrollment (K-12)\`,
    f.\`FRPM Count (K-12)\` / f.\`Enrollment (K-12)\` AS rate
FROM frpm f
JOIN schools s ON f.CDSCode = s.CDSCode
WHERE s.SOC = '66'
  AND f.\`Enrollment (K-12)\` > 0
ORDER BY f.\`FRPM Count (K-12)\` DESC
LIMIT 10;
"
input.description: Get top 10 SOC 66 schools by FRPM Count K-12

content.text:
The results are clear. The top 5 schools by FRPM Count (K-12) with SOC = 66 are:

1. Paramount High — rate: 0.918
2. Calexico High — rate: 0.999
3. Bell Senior High — rate: 0.896
4. Anaheim High — rate: 0.896
5. Bell Gardens High — rate: 0.914
